Indicates the color management mode which will be used during print spool generation. You can choose between RGB and CMYK for color spools and Monochrome for black and white spools. The default value is RGB.

Color management is handled using the **Color **panel of the Target; it is possible to choose between RGB and CMYK color spaces. If the desired color space is CMYK, Document Composition will automatically convert the colors from its internal RGB format using an industry standard algorithm. If a custom conversion is desired, a color profile can be created.

# 
## Accessing the color management
The **Color **tab allows to access and configure font colors.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Option**

**Description**

**Enable Color**

Select to enable color for the spool. Deselect to set the spool to black and white.

**do not use dithering**

Convert colors to a solid black instead of using dithered patterns depending on the color luminosity when monochrome color space is selected.

**Color Space**

Select the color space (only when color is enabled):

- **RGB **

- **CMYK**

## Enabling or disabling a color conversion
- Click the check box in the **Enable **column of the desired conversion. The default color management mode which will be used during print spool generation is to enable color for the spool (RGB color space).

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select **CMYK **to activate the CMYK color space and to enable the custom color conversion profile.

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

- Deselect **Enable color **option to set the spool to black and white.

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

# 
## Customizing the color conversion profile
Color conversion profile information displayed:

**Properties**

**Description**

**Enabled**

The custom conversion is used in the spool only if it is enabled

**Composition color**

RGB color used in the Document Composition compositor

**Corresponding spool color**

Desired CMYK color components. Values are in range 0..100.

### Set the spool to black and white
Deselect **Enable color **option.

### Set the spool to color using RGB color space
- Click **Enable color **option.

- Click **RGB **radio button to activate the RGB color space.

### Set the spool to color using CMYK color space
- Click **Enable color **option.

- Click **CMYK **radio button to activate the CMYK color space.

# Managing the custom color conversion
### Adding a custom color conversion from RGB to CMYK color space
- Click &nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,) to insert a new color conversion.

- Enter CMYK desired values in the conversion.

> Warning

The conversion is used only if the target color space is CMYK and the conversion is enabled

### Deleting a custom color conversion from RGB to CMYK color space
- Click on the conversion to delete.

- Click &nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,) to delete the color conversion.

### Adding a custom color conversion from RGB to spool gray level
- Deselect **Enable color **option.

- Click &nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,) to insert a new color conversion.

- Enter spool gray level desired values in the conversion.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

### Deleting a custom color conversion from RGB to spool gray level
- Click on the conversion to delete.

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,)  to delete the color conversion.

![](data:image/png;base64,)
